verses.text_plain: Knowest thou the time when the wild goats of the rock bring forth? or canst thou mark when the hinds do calve?
verses.verse_html: 1Knowest thou the time when the wild goats of the rock bring forth? or canst thou mark when the hinds do calve?

verses.text_plain: Canst thou number the months that they fulfil? or knowest thou the time when they bring forth?
verses.verse_html: 2Canst thou number the months that they fulfil? or knowest thou the time when they bring forth?

verses.text_plain: They bow themselves, they bring forth their young ones, they cast out their sorrows.
verses.verse_html: 3They bow themselves, they bring forth their young ones, they cast out their sorrows.

verses.text_plain: Their young ones are in good liking, they grow up with corn; they go forth, and return not unto them.
verses.verse_html: 4Their young ones are in good liking, they grow up with corn; they go forth, and return not unto them.

verses.text_plain: Who hath sent out the wild ass free? or who hath loosed the bands of the wild ass?
verses.verse_html: 5Who hath sent out the wild ass free? or who hath loosed the bands of the wild ass?

verses.text_plain: Whose house I have made the wilderness, and the barren land his dwellings.
verses.verse_html:
6Whose house I have made the wilderness, and the barren land his dwellings. ▼
▼ barren…: Heb. salt places

footnotes.body_html: ▼ barren…: Heb. salt places

verses.text_plain: He scorneth the multitude of the city, neither regardeth he the crying of the driver.
verses.verse_html:
7He scorneth the multitude of the city, neither regardeth he the crying of the driver. ▼
▼ of the driver: Heb. of the exactor

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of the driver: Heb. of the exactor
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of the driver: Heb. of the exactor

verses.text_plain: The range of the mountains is his pasture, and he searcheth after every green thing.
verses.verse_html: 8The range of the mountains is his pasture, and he searcheth after every green thing.

verses.text_plain: Will the unicorn be willing to serve thee, or abide by thy crib?
verses.verse_html: 9Will the unicorn be willing to serve thee, or abide by thy crib?

verses.text_plain: Canst thou bind the unicorn with his band in the furrow? or will he harrow the valleys after thee?
verses.verse_html: 10Canst thou bind the unicorn with his band in the furrow? or will he harrow the valleys after thee?

verses.text_plain: Wilt thou trust him, because his strength is great? or wilt thou leave thy labour to him?
verses.verse_html: 11Wilt thou trust him, because his strength is great? or wilt thou leave thy labour to him?

verses.text_plain: Wilt thou believe him, that he will bring home thy seed, and gather it into thy barn?
verses.verse_html: 12Wilt thou believe him, that he will bring home thy seed, and gather it into thy barn?

tokens.text: him, that he will bring home

verses.text_plain: Gavest thou the goodly wings unto the peacocks? or wings and feathers unto the ostrich?
verses.verse_html:
13Gavest thou the goodly wings unto the peacocks? or wings and feathers unto the ostrich? ▼
▼ wings and…: or, the feathers of the stork and ostrich

footnotes.body_text: ▼ wings and…: or, the feathers of the stork and ostrich
footnotes.body_html: ▼ wings and…: or, the feathers of the stork and ostrich

verses.text_plain: Which leaveth her eggs in the earth, and warmeth them in dust,
verses.verse_html: 14Which leaveth her eggs in the earth, and warmeth them in dust,

verses.text_plain: And forgetteth that the foot may crush them, or that the wild beast may break them.
verses.verse_html: 15And forgetteth that the foot may crush them, or that the wild beast may break them.

verses.text_plain: She is hardened against her young ones, as though they were not hers: her labour is in vain without fear;
verses.verse_html: 16She is hardened against her young ones, as though they were not hers: her labour is in vain without fear;

verses.text_plain: Because God hath deprived her of wisdom, neither hath he imparted to her understanding.
verses.verse_html: 17Because God hath deprived her of wisdom, neither hath he imparted to her understanding.

verses.text_plain: What time she lifteth up herself on high, she scorneth the horse and his rider.
verses.verse_html: 18What time she lifteth up herself on high, she scorneth the horse and his rider.

verses.text_plain: Hast thou given the horse strength? hast thou clothed his neck with thunder?
verses.verse_html: 19Hast thou given the horse strength? hast thou clothed his neck with thunder?

verses.text_plain: Canst thou make him afraid as a grasshopper? the glory of his nostrils is terrible.
verses.verse_html:
20Canst thou make him afraid as a grasshopper? the glory of his nostrils is terrible. ▼
▼ terrible: Heb. terror

verses.text_plain: He paweth in the valley, and rejoiceth in his strength: he goeth on to meet the armed men.
verses.verse_html:
21He paweth in the valley, and rejoiceth in his strength: he goeth on to meet the armed men. ▼
▼ He paweth: or, His feet dig
 , ▼
▼ the armed…: Heb. the armour

footnotes.body_text: ▼ He paweth: or, His feet dig
footnotes.body_html: ▼ He paweth: or, His feet dig
▼ the armed…: Heb. the armour

verses.text_plain: He mocketh at fear, and is not affrighted; neither turneth he back from the sword.
verses.verse_html: 22He mocketh at fear, and is not affrighted; neither turneth he back from the sword.

verses.text_plain: The quiver rattleth against him, the glittering spear and the shield.
verses.verse_html: 23The quiver rattleth against him, the glittering spear and the shield.

verses.text_plain: He swalloweth the ground with fierceness and rage: neither believeth he that it is the sound of the trumpet.
verses.verse_html: 24He swalloweth the ground with fierceness and rage: neither believeth he that it is the sound of the trumpet.

verses.text_plain: He saith among the trumpets, Ha, ha; and he smelleth the battle afar off, the thunder of the captains, and the shouting.
verses.verse_html: 25He saith among the trumpets, Ha, ha; and he smelleth the battle afar off, the thunder of the captains, and the shouting.

verses.text_plain: Doth the hawk fly by thy wisdom, and stretch her wings toward the south?
verses.verse_html: 26Doth the hawk fly by thy wisdom, and stretch her wings toward the south?

verses.text_plain: Doth the eagle mount up at thy command, and make her nest on high?
verses.verse_html:
27Doth the eagle mount up at thy command, and make her nest on high? ▼
▼ at…: Heb. by thy mouth

footnotes.body_html: ▼ at…: Heb. by thy mouth

verses.text_plain: She dwelleth and abideth on the rock, upon the crag of the rock, and the strong place.
verses.verse_html: 28She dwelleth and abideth on the rock, upon the crag of the rock, and the strong place.

verses.text_plain: From thence she seeketh the prey, and her eyes behold afar off.
verses.verse_html: 29From thence she seeketh the prey, and her eyes behold afar off.

verses.text_plain: Her young ones also suck up blood: and where the slain are, there is she.
verses.verse_html: 30Her young ones also suck up blood: and where the slain are, there is she.
